The Trump administration has already canceled a $929 million grant issued to the project in 2010 by the Obama administration.
“Any clawback of federal funds already expended on this project would be disastrous policy,” Kelly wrote.
In that span, state Attorney General Xavier Becerra has filed or joined in nearly 50 lawsuits against the Trump administration.
Kelly’s argument that the “clawback” of that much in federal funds would be unprecedented appears correct.
But the state’s arguments are weakened by the difficulty it will face in asserting it acquired the federal funds while acting in good faith.